-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription/month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    event_id,
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/mart/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Calculate monthly subscription metrics by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        be.event_month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(p.monthly_price) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
        ON be.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
    GROUP BY
        be.event_month,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)'),
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)')
)
SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source
ORDER BY
    month DESC,
    tier,
    industry
